<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-09-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="719" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 294.11Ei5/1.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Guthrie</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Request arrest and provisional detention of John Eills, charged with
                            perjury in Massachusetts, where a warrant has been issued for his
                            arrest. The Governor of Massachusetts has been informed that Eills is at
                            Tokio. It is feared that accused may do violence to himself or his
                            daughter, who is with him. Endeavor to have this prevented, Formal
                            papers have already gone forward, and officers will proceed at once to
                            Japan on learning of arrest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>